<m:mi> i </m:mi>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
”. During the motion, however, rod begins to slip away from the axis. As such, mass distribution of the system changes. In other words,  MI of the system changes. But, the angular momentum of the system ("
<m:math>
<m:msub>
