<para id="element-83"><term>Example 5 </term> </para>
<para id="element-84"><term>Problem : </term> A solid sphere of mass 1 kg and radius 10 cm lies on a horizontal surface. A particle of mass 0.01 kg moving with velocity 10 m/s parallel to horizontal surface hits the sphere at a vertical height 6 cm above the center of the sphere and sticks to it. Find (i) the angular velocity of the sphere just after the collision and (ii) the translation velocity of the sphere, if its motion is pure rolling after collision.
</para>
